Class SignatureTree

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.katjahahn.tools.sigscanner.SignatureTree

  • public abstract class SignatureTree
extends java.lang.Object
    A mutable prefix tree for byte signatures. Provides a fast way to match a byte sequence to a large number of signatures

      • hasValue

        protected boolean hasValue(scala.Option<java.lang.Object> b)
        Returns whether the current SignatureTree Node (or Leave) has a value that equals b. A Leave always returns false as it has no value saved.

        Parameters:
        b - an Option byte
        Returns:
        true iff it is a Node and has a value that equals b

      • matchesValue

        protected boolean matchesValue(byte b)
        Returns whether the current SignatureTree Node (or Leave) has a value that matches b (Note: None matches to every Byte). A Leave always returns false as it has no value saved.

        Parameters:
        b - a Byte
        Returns:
        true if the given byte matches the value in the node; that means if the value in the node is a None, it returns true; if the current node is a Leave it returns false
